<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Jenna Coleman might have just been popping to the shops on Monday, but that didn't stop her having a serious fashion moment. </p>

<p>The Victoria star, 34, looked incredible wearing a statement tweed jacket which had an orange pattern running throughout. </p>

<p>Showing off her tanned legs in a pair of black shorts, she opted for comfort wearing a pair of fleece-lined Birkenstock sandals. </p>

<p>Stepping out: Jenna Coleman put on a stunning sartorial display in a statement tweed jacket and shorts as she carried a Union Jack themed Christian Dior book bag</p>

<p>Paying homage to her royal character, Queen Victoria, she carried a very patriotic Union Jack Christian Dior book tote. </p>

<p>The item is currently sold out but can be found on resale sites for up to £3,300.</p>

<p>Jenna looked every inch the superstar wearing her hair down and glossy, along with a dark pair of sunglasses.</p>

<p>Cash splasher: Paying homage to her royal character, Queen Victoria, she carried a very patriotic Union Jack Christian Dior book tote</p>

<p>It's been a tumultuous time for Jenna as earlier this month, she and her ex, fellow actor Tom Hughes, 35, were pictured moving out of their London home.   </p>

<p>The couple shocked fans when they split in July - having been a couple - on and off-screen - for four years.</p>

<p>But things seemed to be made final as the Victoria stars dealt with matters at their former shared property.</p>

<p>The actress and her Victoria co-star fell in love on set while playing the lead roles of Queen Victoria and Prince Albert in the ITV period costume drama. </p>

<p>Over: It's been a tumultuous time for Jenna as earlier this month, she and her ex, fellow actor Tom Hughes, 35, were pictured moving out of their London home</p>

<p>But they are thought to be keeping things amicable between them. </p>

<p>An insider told The Sun that the pair have since met up in an attempt to keep things 'as friendly and civil as possible.' </p>

<p>The source said: 'They are trying to salvage a friendship but obviously these are trying times, and it's not easy. </p>

<p>'Both Tom and Jenna are terribly sad, but the relationship ran its course. There was no third party involved.  </p>

<p>'Jenna's career is going from strength to strength, she's being offered increasingly more roles abroad, especially Los Angeles, and she wants to focus on this while she's still young.' </p>

